# 🧠 HYBRID ARCHITECTURE (KEY DESIGN)

## 1. 24H PERFORMANCE
Instead of an expensive in-memory JS grouping, we use a single SQL `GROUP BY wallet` on indexed `trades`. This results in **sub-100ms response times** even as data scales.

## 2. ALL-TIME (OVERALL) PERFORMANCE
We precompute scores every 24h into `leaderboard_stats` so that the overall view is a simple `ORDER BY score DESC` on an indexed column.

## 3. PROFESSIONAL EDGE CACHING
Using `stale-while-revalidate` (SWR) headers, users always get a fast response from the CDN while the server refreshes stale data in the background.

